<DOC><DOCNO> AP890903-0002 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-03-89 2353EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-Israel-Lebanon     09-03 0210</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Israel-Lebanon,0216</SECOND><HEAD>Israel Bombs Guerrilla Base in South Lebanon</HEAD><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Israeli warplanes destroyed a guerrilla base insouth Lebanon 21 miles north of the Israeli border Monday, the armysaid.   All planes returned safely from the early morning raid, amilitary statement said.   An army spokesman said the planes struck a guerrilla base in thevillage of Majdal Balhis, about three miles east of Mashghara. Thespokesman, who is not identified under military regulations, wouldnot say which militia operated the base nor give the reason for theraid.   The air raid follows attacks Wednesday and Thursday in whichKatyusha rockets were fired at Israel's Galilee district from southLebanon. The attacks caused no injuries, but one rocket damaged ahouse in Kiryat Shmona in the Galilee Panhandle.   Israeli authorities blamed that rocket attack on the militantShiite Moslem militia Hezbollah, or Party of God.   Also on Thursday, Israeli troops fought a battle with fourguerrillas just north of the border, and one member of the Shiitemilitia Amal was killed. Israel suffered no casualties in thefirefight.   The air attack was the the 10th time Israeli war planes havestruck in Lebanon this year. The last raid, on Aug. 27, was aimed ata Hezbollah base.</TEXT></DOC>